      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "The Zigmond chamber [CITATION_1] is similar to the Boyden chamber in that a gradient is formed by the diffusion of chemotactic factor between two chambers (Fig. 1B, Table 1) ; however in the Zigmond chamber, the permeable membrane of the Boyden chamber separating the two sources of chemotactic cue is replaced by a narrow space."
